hivis.data.view

Interface GroupedTable<K>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Data, DataMap<K,TableView>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultGroupedTable

    public interface GroupedTable<K>
extends DataMap<K,TableView>

    Represents a view of a DataTable containing the rows collected into groups. The grouping is represented as a DataMap where the map keys represent the group identifier or key and the map values are DataTables containing the rows belonging to that group.

    The rows in the group tables appear in the same order as their order in the original table.

    The group tables returned by get(Object) and DataMap.values() are emptied (set to length 0) if the group size becomes zero (and calls to get(Object) for groups that do not yet exist will return empty group tables, but not add them to the list of group tables returned by DataMap.values() ). If the group size subsequently becomes non-zero this same group table will be reused. This allows external observers to monitor the size of a group even if it may become empty, and before it has existed in the input table.

    Author:
    O. J. Coleman
    See Also:
    DataTable.group(int), DataTable.group(String)

    • Method Detail

      • get

        TableView get(K key)
        Get the group table for the specified group identifier/key. If the key does not currently exist then an empty table will be returned. If the group for the key subsequently becomes non-empty then the previously returned table will be populated accordingly.
        Specified by:
        get in interface DataMap<K,TableView>

      • aggregate

        TableView aggregate(AggregateFunction function)

        Creates a view of the table groups in which each group table is aggregated into a single row using the specified aggregation function.

        The AggregateFunction.apply(String, hivis.data.DataSeries) method of the given AggregateFunction will be called for each series in each group table, and the resulting value used for the corresponding series and row for the group table in the returned table.

        Parameters:
        function - The aggregation function.

      • aggregateMin

        TableView aggregateMin()
        Convenience aggregation method (see aggregate(AggregateFunction) . The aggregation function returns the minimum value of each series in a given group table, or the first value of the series if it's not numeric.
